@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual ---------------------------------------------- Introduction -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Main" "Introduction"
@{U}1) Introduction@{UU}

   Laplace is (or at least should be) an universal tool for mathematical  cal-
culations. It lacks such a GUI with hundreds of windows like those other progs
I've found for the AMIGA. Instead it  works like a shell: you enter a  command
and get the result displayed, which is (imho) much more flexible.

   I started programming Laplace, because I was looking for a program for han-
dling matrices, something I needed for my studies. First all programs I  found
were only able to handle floatpoints, but especially with matrix  calculations
this will  lead quite  fast to  large errors.  So I  made a  simple prog  that
handled fractions instead  of floatpoints.  After that I  needed something  to
handle parameters in matrices, and so  I totally rewrote Laplace. This is  the
result.

