@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual -------------------------------------------- Reporting bugs -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Introduction" "Reporting bugs"
@{U}1.3) Reporting bugs@{UU}

   If you find a bug, something that works not as described in the manual,  or
Laplace refuses to start at all, it would  be a great help for me, if you  re-
port this to me, so I can fix  it. Laplace grew to be an enormous project  and
it's impossible for a single person like me to test it in all possible  situa-
tions.

   I prepared  a form  for a  bug report,  you can  find it  in the  directory
@{B}Docs/english@{UB}. A small  script is  executed that creates  a text  file that  is
saved under @{B}RAM:Bug.txt@{UB}. Load  this file into  a text editor  and fill in  the
gaps. Try give  a detailed explanation  of the bug,  e.g. the expression  that
leads to a wrong result, which menu item you selected etc.

   If you have an MMU installed, you  can install the tools ENFORCER and  SEG-
TRACKER. If ENFORCER than  generates some output  regarding Laplace, save  the
output and append it to the bug report.

   Than send the file to me, either by  e-mail or print it out and post it  to
me.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ © by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
