@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual ------------------------------------------ Where to find it -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Introduction" "Where to find it"
@{U}1.4) Where to find it@{UU}

   The distribution of Laplace is splited into five archives

 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}LaplaceBase.lha@{UB}
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}Laplace000.lha@{UB}
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}Laplace020.lha@{UB}
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}Laplace020fp.lha@{UB}
 @{B}·@{UB} @{B}Laplace040.lha@{UB}

   You always need the first file @{B}LaplaceBase.lha@{UB}, it contains all data  files
needed by Laplace, the documentation and the installation script.

   The program itself exists in  three different versions, optimized for  dif-
ferent processors. Depending on the processor  of your AMIGA, you need one  of
the other three files:

 @{B}·@{UB} Use @{B}Laplace000.lha@{UB}, if you have an AMIGA with a MC68000 processor  (e.g.
   a AMIGA500 or AMIGA2000  without a processor  card). This version  works
   for higher processors, too,  but it doesn't make  use of their  advanced
   instruction set (and is thereby slower).
 @{B}·@{UB} Use @{B}Laplace020.lha@{UB}, if you have a processor MC68020, MC68030, MC68040 or
   MC68060, but no floatpoint unit (e.g. AMIGA1200 in it's base  configura-
   tion). Floatpoint operations are emulated by the processor, which can be
   terribly slow.
 @{B}·@{UB} Use @{B}Laplace020fp.lha@{UB} with a processor MC68020 or higher and an  attached
   floatpoint unit. This gives you the maximum performance.
 @{B}·@{UB} Use @{B}Laplace040.lha@{UB} with the MC68040 processor. This will only use  those
   floatpoint instructions that are supported by the processor.



   These archives can  be found at  different places. The  most common way  is
probably the AMINET; Laplace can be found in the directory @{B}misc/math/@{UB}. This is
always the first place, where the latest version of Laplace appears.

   If you don't have access to the INTERNET, wait for the next release of  the
AMINET-CD. It is a  collection of the  latest uploads to  the AMINET, and  you
will thereby find Laplace on it, too  (if there was no new version of  Laplace
since the last release of the AMINET-CD, the CD is still worth buying!).

   If you have neither  a CD-ROM drive  nor access to  the INTERNET, there  is
still a last possibility. I could send  you the latest release on a  diskette.
The first disk if free, if you order it along with a @{"registration" LINK "Registration"}  (smile...).
If you are not registered,  you have to pay DM10  for the first time, and  DM5
for each following release.  The easiest way to  submit such small amounts  of
cash to me, is to put it into an envelope and send it to

                              Benjamin Stegemann
                              Scheffelstraße 14
                               69214 Eppelheim
                                   Germany

   A remittance is probably too expensive.  Because you cannot find DM5  notes
anymore, and sending a DM5 coin would  be too dangerous, send DM10 instead.  I
will then send the actual version of Laplace, and the next release as soon  as
it appears. Feel free to send even higher amounts, you will then get a new re-
lease of Laplace as soon as it appears until your @{I}account @{UI} is empty.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ © by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
