@REM KEY 0 0 "Introduction" "Address"
@{U}1.6) Address@{UU}

   To reach me, the author of this @{I}fantastic @{UI} program, write to

                              Benjamin Stegemann
                              Scheffelstraße 14
                               69214 Eppelheim
                                   Germany

   As you  can  see,  my address  has  changed.  So  if you  have  sent  me  a
letter/postcard in the  time of  April '97 until  now, it  didn't reached  me.
Sorry about that, but I simply forgot it...

   Still this address is only temporary, I'm currently living in the house  of
some friends until I found a  room for myself (I had  to leave my flat at  the
end of March '98 again). But letters will reach me (with some delay), even  if
I have a new address, thereby you can use it until I publish a new one.

   If you prefer electronic mail, send it to

                      bstegema@ix.urz.uni-heidelberg.de

   If you want a fast reply, write a postcard! If you add your e-mail  address
I will probably  use it  to reply,  but in most  cases a  postcard reaches  me
faster than an e-mail (that's why it's called @{I}s-mail @{UI}: speed-mail!!!).


